sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ChlOp3
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This operon codes for chlorophyll(a) when combined with BBa_K1080026 and BBa_K1080027, and is combined with a Ptac promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Macquarie University

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K864400
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Created from oligos ordered from SigmaAldrich.
Oligo sequences: Ptac+ AATTCGCGGCCGCTTCTAGAGGAGCTGTTGACAATTAATCATCGGCTCGTATAATGTGTGGAATTGTGAGCGGATAACAATTTA
Ptac- CTAGTAAATTGTTATCCGCTCACAATTCCACACATTATACGAGCCGATGATTAATTGTCAACAGCTCCTCTAGAAGCGGCCGCG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Ptac promoter is a functional hybrid promoter, derived from the trp and lac promoters, that are regulated by trp and lac [1]. This part also exist together with lacI, part [[Part:BBa_K180000|BBa_K180000]]
[1] Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, Vol. 80, pp. 21-25
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Oligos ordered from SigmaAldrich were annealed to form a double stranded DNA segment, ready to be ligated into any BioBrick backbone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Lundin
